<div id="review_1002475277" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1002475277" />
    <a title="Gary " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27528763-gary"><img alt="Gary " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1499717454p2/27528763.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1002475277?book_show_action=true">Oct 28, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gary " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gary " href="/user/show/27528763-gary">Gary </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27528763-gary?shelf=crime">crime</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27528763-gary?shelf=psychological-mind-games">psychological-mind-games</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27528763-gary?shelf=series-worth-continuing">series-worth-continuing</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1002475277" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14516359815236936800">This was an excellent book. I have been looking for a series like this for awhile and I hear through the Goodreads grapevine it keeps getting better.<br/>The main character, Charlie Parker, has had some dark things built into his past- and I do mean dark. Guilt ridden, suicidal and horrifyingly dark. This is part of what opens him to the reader. It creates a sympathy for his approach which is often a whatever means necessary to solve a problem.<br/> A big part of the hook in this series is my interest in </span>
  <span id="freeText14516359815236936800" style="display:none">This was an excellent book. I have been looking for a series like this for awhile and I hear through the Goodreads grapevine it keeps getting better.<br />The main character, Charlie Parker, has had some dark things built into his past- and I do mean dark. Guilt ridden, suicidal and horrifyingly dark. This is part of what opens him to the reader. It creates a sympathy for his approach which is often a whatever means necessary to solve a problem.<br /> A big part of the hook in this series is my interest in what happens next to Parker. The author weaves a dark psychological perspective into his story and there are times I get lost in the musing or the diction and it becomes as important as the plot itself.<br />Five out of five stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14516359815236936800" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
